Rockingham, )

May 1, 1906. ( Barsantee v. Hartford. Case, for libel. Transferred from the April term, 1905, of the superior court by Stone, J. Page Bartlett and Brnest L. Gruptill, for the plaintiff. Prink, Marvin Batchelder, for the defendant. Walker, J.

The questions presented arise upon the defendant’s exceptions to the admission of evidence. In the absence of *617a brief in support of tbe exceptions, or other information from the defendant relating to his legal positions, no error is perceived and the exceptions are therefore overruled.

All concurred.
